timms-storage
=============

This project is a replacement for all the design and household management
software out there that is either bloated, locked behind paywalls, or just
not built for normal people.

Most existing tools do one thing well and everything else poorly. This one
is supposed to change that. The goal is simple software that actually works,
respects the user, and does not require a subscription or an account on
someones server to function.

Built desktop-first. Written in Rust.


What is wrong with existing software
-------------------------------------

- Features are scattered across five different apps
- Mobile versions are either broken or an afterthought
- Adding items manually takes forever
- No connection to real stores or product databases
- Cloud sync is mandatory and often opaque
- Most tools assume you are a professional or a developer


What this project wants to fix
--------------------------------

- One place for household management, shopping lists, and pantry tracking
- Barcode scanning to add items without typing everything by hand
- Integration with open product databases like Open Food Facts
- Store awareness via OpenStreetMap so you know where to buy what
- Local-first, your data stays on your device
- Simple enough for anyone to use on day one


Contributing
-------------

Contributions are very welcome. Seriously, if you have an idea, a fix, or
just an opinion on how something should work, open an issue or send a patch.
This project is better with more people involved and I mean that.


Status
-------

Early development. Things will break. The name will probably change too.


